Errr, if you are currently swapping a class you are in or waitlisted for another class that would put you on the waitlist, the second class shouldn't count towards your units. 

-----

It seems like it does count, but swapping itself doesn't check. So, you can go above the unit cap via a swap, but until the swap is completed, both courses would count towards your unit cap.

-----

^ you would assume that this shiny new enrollment system would have logic to make swaps atomic - i.e. only count the currently enrolled class until the swap actually occurs. Guess we can't have our cake and eat it too
